$ System.IO (namespace)

The `System.IO` namespace provides classes that are used in relation to files and directories.

Some commonly used classes of this namespace include
  • → Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/IO/File[`System.IO.File`] and → Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/IO/Directory[`System.IO.Directory`]
  • → Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/IO/FileInfo[`System.IO.FileInfo`] and → Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/IO/DirectoryInfo[`System.IO.DirectoryInfo`]
  • → Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/IO/Path[`System.IO.Path`]
  • Classes that inherit from the abstract class → Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/IO/Stream[`System.IO.Stream`] which provide reading and writing → development/Data. A stream's three fundamental operations are: read, write and seek.

links:
  → https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/standard/io/common-i-o-tasks[Common I/O tasks]
